    </div>

    <div>
      <strong>Master's Thesis: Galactic Synchrotron Radiation</strong> (2024 - 2025) — NISER Bhubaneswar, India<br/>
      Studied statistical properties of Galactic synchrotron radiation using physical models and tools like power spectrum, Minkowski Functionals, higher-order cumulants, etc.<br/>
      Supervisor: <a href="https://www.niser.ac.in/~tghosh" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Dr. Tuhin Ghosh</a>
    </div>

    <div>
      <strong>Summer 2024: Dark Matter Halo Merger Trees</strong> — NORDITA<br/>
      Studied dark matter halo merger trees for different cosmologies using the GALFORM algorithm.<br/>
      Supervisor: <a href="#" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Dr. Sambit Giri</a>
    </div>

    <div>
      <strong>Independent Research Project: SALSA</strong> (2023 - 2024) — NISER Bhubaneswar<br/>
      Developed Self-Supervised Active Learning Search Algorithm to efficiently explore latent spaces and minority class sampling.<br/>
      Supervisor: <a href="https://www.niser.ac.in/~smishra" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Dr. Subhankar Mishra</a>
    </div>

    <div>
      <strong>Summer 2023: Galactic Magnetic Field Studies</strong> — IIA Bengaluru, NISER Bhubaneswar<br/>
      Investigated Galactic Magnetic Field properties and simulated synchrotron maps using gpempy module.<br/>
      Supervisors: 
      <a href="#" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Dr. Pravabati Chingangbam</a>, 
      <a href="https://www.niser.ac.in/~tghosh" target="_blank" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">Dr. Tuhin Ghosh</a>
    </div>

    <div>
      <strong>Summer 2022: X-ray spectra of Dual AGNs</strong> — IIA Bengaluru<br/>
      Analysed Fe K spectral signatures in a binary AGN system, published in Astronomy & Astrophysics.<br/>
      Supervisors: 
